8/8 ❌ Disqualification alert: Leaving the test screen/tab, talking to someone, or not turning on your camera will get you an instant one-way ticket out. Don’t be that person.

7/8 🖥️ You can use a PC or mobile phone for the test, but trust me, a PC is your best bet. You don't want your ex calling your phone during a test. Do you?

No one likes surprises, especially not during this test.
6/8 👀 The test platform will be monitoring your screen and your face. And it’ll trigger a ‘cheating’ alert if you leave the screen/tab or chat with anyone. Which might get you disqualified.
5/8 📸 Your camera must be on, and you should be in a well-lit spot. This isn’t a photoshoot, but we still need to see your face. It’s part of our anti-cheat and fairness protocols.
4/8 📶 Make sure your internet is top-notch. A 2G internet is the last thing you need today—unless you enjoy frustration 😅
3/8 🧠 The questions are basic and surface-level for a genius like you. Nothing too deep or soul-crushing, just some general cognitive stuff and a few questions specific to your skills. You got this!

2/8 ⏰ You will receive the test link in your email within 1:55PM to 2 PM. You’ve got 1 hour to complete the test, but the link will only be open for 1 hour and 15 minutes. That extra 15 minutes? Yeah, that’s your grace period—so don’t snooze on it!
